"Preserves" is a category of fruit spread for your morning toast, the same as JAM.  If you were a server in a restaurant, you may bring out some fruit spreads and tell your customer, "This is grape jam, and this is strawberry preserves."

So in short, "preserves" is plural in form but serves as a mass (non-count) noun, the way "jam" does.  That is, you never say "seven preserves."

